# 2. Algebra II

## Polynomials

| Concept | Formula |
|------|--------|
| Degree | highest power of \(x\) |
| Quadratic | \( ax^2+bx+c \) |
| Cubic | \( ax^3+bx^2+cx+d \) |

---

## Factoring Identities

| Identity | Formula |
|--------|--------|
| Difference of squares | \( a^2-b^2=(a-b)(a+b) \) |
| Sum of cubes | \( a^3+b^3=(a+b)(a^2-ab+b^2) \) |
| Difference of cubes | \( a^3-b^3=(a-b)(a^2+ab+b^2) \) |

---

## Quadratics

| Tool | Formula |
|----|--------|
| Quadratic formula | \( x=\frac{-b\pm\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a} \) |
| Discriminant | \( \Delta=b^2-4ac \) |
| Vertex | \( x=-\frac{b}{2a} \) |
| Completing square | \( ax^2+bx+c=a(x+\frac{b}{2a})^2+(c-\frac{b^2}{4a}) \) |

---

## Polynomial Division

| Rule | Formula |
|----|--------|
| Division algorithm | \( P(x)=D(x)Q(x)+R(x) \) |
| Remainder theorem | remainder of \(P(x)/(x-c)=P(c)\) |
| Factor theorem | \( P(c)=0 \iff (x-c)\mid P(x) \) |
| Partial fractions | \( \frac{P(x)}{(x-a)(x-b)}=\frac{A}{x-a}+\frac{B}{x-b} \) |

---

## Linear Systems (Intro Matrix View)

| Concept | Formula |
|------|--------|
| Linear system | \( Ax=b \) |
| 2×2 determinant | \( ad-bc \) |
| 2×2 inverse | \( \frac1{\det A}\begin{pmatrix}d&-b\\-c&a\end{pmatrix} \) |

