# 3. Calculus

## Limits

| Concept | Formula |
|------|--------|
| Limit | \( \lim_{x\to a}f(x)=L \) |
| One-sided | \( \lim_{x\to a^-},\ \lim_{x\to a^+} \) |
| ε–δ | \( |x-a|<\delta \Rightarrow |f(x)-L|<\varepsilon \) |

---

## Derivatives

| Function | Derivative |
|--------|------------|
| Constant | \( 0 \) |
| \( x^n \) | \( nx^{n-1} \) |
| \( e^x \) | \( e^x \) |
| \( \ln x \) | \( 1/x \) |
| \( \sin x \) | \( \cos x \) |
| \( \cos x \) | \( -\sin x \) |

---

## Differentiation Rules

| Rule | Formula |
|----|--------|
| Definition | \( f'(x)=\lim_{h\to0}\frac{f(x+h)-f(x)}{h} \) |
| Product | \( (fg)'=f'g+fg' \) |
| Quotient | \( (f/g)'=\frac{f'g-fg'}{g^2} \) |
| Chain | \( \frac{d}{dx}f(g(x))=f'(g(x))g'(x) \) |

---

## Integrals

| Concept | Formula |
|------|--------|
| Indefinite | \( \int f'(x)\,dx=f(x)+C \) |
| Power rule | \( \int x^n dx=\frac{x^{n+1}}{n+1}+C \) |
| Definite | \( \int_a^b f(x)\,dx=F(b)-F(a) \) |
| Substitution | \( \int f(g(x))g'(x)\,dx=\int f(u)\,du \) |

---

## Multivariable Calculus

| Concept | Formula |
|------|--------|
| Partial | \( \frac{\partial f}{\partial x_i} \) |
| Gradient | \( \nabla f=[\partial f/\partial x_1,\dots,\partial f/\partial x_n]^\top \) |
| Directional | \( D_u f=\nabla f^\top u \) |
| Jacobian | \( J_{ij}=\frac{\partial f_i}{\partial x_j} \) |
| Hessian | \( H_{ij}=\frac{\partial^2 f}{\partial x_i\partial x_j} \) |

---

## Taylor Approximation

| Order | Formula |
|----|--------|
| First | \( f(x+h)\approx f(x)+\nabla f^\top h \) |
| Second | \( f(x+h)\approx f(x)+\nabla f^\top h+\frac12 h^\top Hh \) |

